        <h1>5. <%= @your_option_page_title_5 %></h1>
      </header>

      <div id="govspeak">
        <p>
          You can use your pension pot to buy a guaranteed income for the rest of your life.
          This is called an annuity. It guarantees you a regular income until you die, even
          if your pension pot runs out of money.
        </p>

        <p>
          You hand over your pension pot to an insurance company and they pay you a retirement
          income in return. Once you’ve you’ve bought your annuity you can’t change this decision.
        </p>

        <div class="application-notice info-notice">
          <p>You don’t have to use your whole pension pot to buy an annuity. You can mix your options.</p>
        </div>

        <p>How much money you get depends on things like:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>how much you have in your pension pot</li>
          <li>your age and gender</li>
          <li>interest rates</li>
          <li>your health and lifestyle</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          You <a href="/tax-on-your-pension/1">pay tax on payments from an annuity</a>,
          just like you do on your salary. You’ll also pay administration charges to
          your annuity provider.
        </p>

        <p>You can also buy an annuity that’s only for a fixed amount of years.</p>

        <p>
          If you want to pass your annuity payments on to your spouse or partner
          you’ll have to buy a joint annuity. This means that payments during your
          lifetime will be lower.
        </p>
      </div>

